{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require online account deletion to be simple and clear",
        "additional_details": "We believe that some companies deliberately make it difficult to delete accounts by hiding the option in obscure menus or requiring unnecessary steps like contacting support or multiple email verifications.\r\n\r\nWe call for a law that mandates:\r\n1. Easy navigation to account settings.\r\n2. A clear, one-step \u201cDelete Account\u201d button.\r\n3. A ban on unnecessary hurdles, ensuring user autonomy and data control.\r\n\r\nWe would like simpler, transparent account deletion for all.",
        "background": "Creating online accounts is simple, but deleting them can be difficult. We would like the government to introduce a law requiring a clear, one-step \u201cDelete Account\u201d button, banning barriers, and ensuring users control their data.",
